{[%evp 0,21,31,19,12,4,31,13,50,50,45,45,45,45,42,24,24,15,27,45,44,45,31,3]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 Nc6 {The Two Knights' Tango or the Mexican Defense. This opening is famous for the game: Marshall-Torre Repetto, 0-1, Baden-Baden 1925, where the Mexican Grandmaster managed to win in just 7 moves!} 3. Nc3 $5 {My idea is simple, to wait for ...d7-d5 and transpose to the Chigorin line.} (3. Nf3 {This is a possible option.} e6 4. a3 d6 $5 {Black's independent idea.} (4... d5 {transposes to the Chigorin Opening.}) 5. Nc3 g6 6. e4 {Strong players used this opening for both sides.} Bg7 7. Bg5 {We are following Kramnik-Caruana, 1-0, Moscow Tal Memorial Blitz 2012.} h6 8. Be3 Ng4 $5 {The only interesting try.} (8... O-O 9. h3 $16 {Kramnik was just better and later won.}) 9. Bc1 O-O (9... f5 $5 $146 {deserves attention, for a very unclear battle.}) 10. h3 Nf6 11. Be3 {We transpose to the game.} e5 12. d5 Nd4 13. Nxd4 exd4 14. Qxd4 $1 {Improvement over the game.} Ng4 15. hxg4 $1 $146 {[%csl Gg4] Typical queen sacrifice, this is the point.} Bxd4 16. Bxd4 $16 {[%csl Gd4,Rg8,Rh6][%cal Gh1h6] White is better thanks to the strong coordination.}) 3... e5 $5 {[%csl Be5] The main line.} (3... d5 4. Nf3 {We transpose to the Chigorin.}) (3... d6 $6 {leads to a bad version of the KID.} 4. d5 Nb8 5. e4 $16 {White is better, not much to analyze, you can play as you wish.}) 4. d5 Ne7 {Most logical.} (4... Nb8 {Not critical, of course.} 5. Nf3 d6 6. e4 $16 {You have a tempo up KID, not much to say about it. Just better for White.}) 5. Nf3 $5 {[%csl Ge2] No need to play e4 early.} d6 (5... Ng6 6. h4 $1 {[%csl Rg6][%cal Gh4h5] Typical move to destabilize the knight.} h5 7. a3 a5 8. Qc2 $146 {[%cal Gg2g3,Gf1g2,Gc1g5] Position is new, the evaluation is also very pleasant for White. Around +1.}) 6. e4 {[%csl Rd6][%cal Rf8c5] This is okay now, since no Bc5 or Bb4 to worry about.} Ng6 {Line used very often by GM Demchenko.} 7. g3 $5 {[%csl Gg3] Difficult to say what is the best move, you should just find a suitable move for your style.} Be7 8. h4 $1 {[%csl Rg6,Gh4] Good inclusion against the knight.} h6 9. Be2 {was tried by GM Andreikin, good move.} c6 10. a4 $1 $146 {[%cal Ga4a5] This is probably a nice plan for White, to get space on the queenside also.} a5 11. Nh2 $16 {[%cal Gc1e3,Gd1b3] White is better, no need to investigate further, it's like a very bad version of the KID for Black.} *

