{[#]} {[%tqu "En","White to move.","","","a2a3","This move is very rare, but very venomous. It's an useful prophylactic and also supports the b4 push.",10,"g2g3","The main move, but it doesn't really offer an advantage:",0,"d4b3","Common choice, but engines have reevaluated this line.",0]} 7. a3 $5 {[%csl Ga3] This move is very rare, but very venomous. It's an useful prophylactic and also supports the b4 push.} (7. g3 {The main move, but it doesn't really offer an advantage:} e5 $1 {[%csl Ge5,Gf6,Rg3] With the g3-Nf6 moves included, this makes more sense.} 8. Nb3 Qc7 {[%csl Rh1][%cal Rc3b5,Gc7c6] The difference is that Nb5 doesn't work now.} 9. Bg2 Bb4 $1 $132 {[%csl Rc3][%cal Gb4e1] To pin the knight, Black is doing okay, and in fact Mamedyarov scored pretty well with this line in blitz games.}) (7. Nb3 {Common choice, but engines have reevaluated this line.} Qc7 $132) 7... e5 8. Nb3 Qc7 9. Nb5 $5 $146 {[%csl Bb5] This is our main recommendation. It's a novelty, and Black must have very serious knowledge and understanding, just to SURVIVE the opening phase!} *

